<TITLE> Hasina release was 'first step' to building broader consensus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnews24.com)Releasing Awami League president Sheikh Hasina has helped all concerned to identify and determine ways of negotiating the present political impasse, said education and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman Thursday. Speaking to reporters at the communication ministry, after a meeting with communication adviser Ghulam Quader, Hossain Zillur said: "Sheikh Hasina's release from custody has constituted one crucial step taken towards resolving the current crisis." "We are now preparing to negotiate the next steps," said the adviser. On the possibility of releasing Khaleda Zia and her two sons, Tarique Rahman and Arafat Rahman Coco, Zillur said: "The government is considering the legal and humanitarian aspects of the matter to reach a decision without wasting any more time." "Meantime, we'll carry on with the meaningful discussions for building a national consensus in addressing the crucial challenges we are facing today." Asked to comment on the timeframe under which the government might be sending Khaleda, Tarique and Coco abroad, the adviser said: "It's difficult to say anything certainly at this stage. I feel we've to travel long distances, but we'll surely do that for the wellbeing of the nation." Asked to comment on the issue, Ghulam Quader said: "We all have to be patient and wait for the best results." "It's not possible for us to share everything with you all the time, though we try to communicate things at the opportune moment." The two advisers later left for the office of law adviser AF Hassan Ariff, where the home affairs adviser joined them in further discussions. bdnews24.
